ging; an estimated 14%-18% of the forests the owl inhabits have been lost in the last decade. This species is also threatened by capture and sale in illegal wildlife trade. Diet While not extensively studied, the diet of the reddish scops owl consists of primarily arthropods and small vertebrates. Breeding The reddish scops owl nests in tree cavities. On Java, eggs of the species have been found in March and April, with a nestling present by mid-July. References BirdLife Species Factsheet ITIS Report", "shortSummary": "The reddish scops owl (Otus rufescens) is an owl found in southeast Asia, in the countries of Thailand, Malaysia, Indonesia, and Brunei. De…", "locations": ["托马斯·霍斯菲尔德", "东南亚", "汶莱"], "habitats": ["沼泽"], "threats": ["栖息地破坏", "森林砍伐"], "lat": 15.0, "lng": 101.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/67/Reddish_scops_owl_%28Otus_rufescens%29_02.jpg/960px-Reddish_scops_owl_%28Otus_rufescens%29_02.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-otus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-otus-rufescens", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-otus", "species": "taxonomy-species-otus-rufescens"}, "expandable": true, "x": -650.02, "y": -300.63, "z": 248.07}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-otus-rufescens", "name": "Reddish scops owl", "latinName": "Otus rufescens", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Reddish scops owl（Otus rufescens）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Reddish scops owl。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -650.02, "y": -300.63, "z": 259.76}], "links": [{"key": "bird-reddish-scops-owl-7ebf8cf7__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-otus-rufescens", "source": "bird-reddish-scops-owl-7ebf8cf7", "target": "taxonomy-species-otus-rufescens", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": 